1. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper investigates information cascades in social networks such as Reddit, Youtube, and Digg. 
2. cs.SD (Software Engineering) - The paper discusses the dynamics of votes and comments on online platforms, which can be related to software engineering practices. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper uses ultrametricity and ultradiffusion to model information propagation, which can be related to systems and control. 
4. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper uses simulations to validate the proposed model, which can be related to computational engineering. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the counting process of votes and comments, which can be related to data structures and algorithms.
